#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:182
msgid ""
"VTK's SOA (structure-of-arrays) layout stores each component in a separate "
"contiguous buffer.  This mixin exposes those per-component buffers as **zero-"
"copy numpy arrays** and performs element-wise operations per-component, "
"avoiding the overhead of converting to AOS layout."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:188
msgid ""
"This mixin is automatically applied to all ``vtkSOADataArrayTemplate`` "
"instantiations.  Any SOA array that crosses from C++ to Python is already a "
"``VTKSOAArray`` instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:192
msgid ""
"Properties/home/runner/work/vtk-docs-l10n/vtk-docs-l10n/out/repo/Wrapping/"
"Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:192: (INFO/1) Duplicate "
"implicit target name: \"properties\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:194
msgid ""
"shape : tuple of int     ``(ntuples,)`` for 1-component, ``(ntuples, "
"ncomps)`` otherwise. dtype : numpy.dtype     The element data type. "
"components : list of numpy.ndarray     Per-component zero-copy numpy array "
"views. dataset : vtkDataSet or None     The owning VTK dataset, when the "
"array is attached to one. association : int or None     The attribute "
"association (POINT, CELL, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:205
msgid ""
"Per-Component Operations/home/runner/work/vtk-docs-l10n/vtk-docs-l10n/out/"
"repo/Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:205: "
"(INFO/1) Duplicate implicit target name: \"per-component operations\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:207
msgid ""
"Arithmetic, comparisons, and ufuncs operate on each component buffer "
"independently, preserving the SOA layout in the result. This avoids the "
"memory overhead and cache penalty of interleaving components into AOS form::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:212
msgid ""
"arr = soa_filter.GetOutput().GetPointData().GetArray(0)\n"
"scaled = arr * 2.0          # per-component multiply, stays SOA\n"
"diff = arr1 - arr2          # per-component subtract\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:216
msgid ""
"When an operation cannot be decomposed per-component (e.g. cross-component "
"reductions with ``axis=1``), the mixin materialises a contiguous AOS copy "
"via ``numpy.column_stack``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:220
msgid ""
"Memory Safety/home/runner/work/vtk-docs-l10n/vtk-docs-l10n/out/repo/Wrapping/"
"Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:220: (INFO/1) Duplicate "
"implicit target name: \"memory safety\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:222
msgid ""
"The mixin observes ``BufferChangedEvent`` from VTK.  If any component buffer "
"is reallocated, the cached views are automatically invalidated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:226
msgid ""
"NumPy Integration/home/runner/work/vtk-docs-l10n/vtk-docs-l10n/out/repo/"
"Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:226: (INFO/1) "
"Duplicate implicit target name: \"numpy integration\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:228
msgid "``numpy.asarray(arr)`` materialises an AOS copy via column_stack."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:229
msgid ""
"Reductions (``sum``, ``mean``, ``min``, ``max``, ``std``, ``var``) operate "
"per-component without materialisation when possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:231
msgid ""
"``numpy.concatenate``, ``numpy.where``, ``numpy.clip``, etc. have SOA-aware "
"overrides."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:233
msgid ""
"The ``__buffer__`` override (PEP 688) prevents ``GetVoidPointer`` from "
"destructively converting SOA storage to AOS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../Wrapping/Python/vtkmodules/numpy_interface/vtk_soa_array.py:236
msgid ""
"Examples/home/runner/work/vtk-docs-l10n/vtk-docs-l10n/out/repo/Wrapping/"
